http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/title.value: Nevada Academic Content Standards for Physical Education

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: A Physically active and educated person is one who has mastered the necessary movement skills to participate confidently in many different forms of physical activity. Even before birth, children begin learning to move and learn about their world through sensory (i.e. kinesthetic) awareness and movement. The process continues from childhood through adolescence and well into late adulthood. A physically educated person values physical fitness and understands its relationship to health and well being. He or she participates regularly in physical activity and understands the benefits of involvement in physical activity.
Demonstrate competency in motor skills, movement patterns and safety needed to perform a variety of physical activities.
